    "KS outperforms SN on dataset sizes 25GB and 100GB; however, this trend reverses with the 1B size dataset.",
    "The difference in distance calculations between SN and KS on the 25GB and 1B datasets is ∼1M and ∼10M, respectively.",
    "As the dataset size increases, it becomes imperative to sample more nodes (beyond the beam width utilized during search in KS) to obtain a representative sample of the dataset, thereby enhancing the likelihood of initiating the search closer to the graph region where the query resides (SN adapts its size logarithmically with the growth of the dataset, leading to a better representation of the Deep1M Deep25GB Dist.",
